field.value:
Basically, when there is a default (i.e., unnamed) top-level controller (called just Controller) and the name of the virtual directory is the empty string, MonoRail was incorrectly declaring the URL invalid.

The Fix

In UrlTokenizer, line 53 where it says if (parts.Length < 2), check for empty string virtual directory

if ( parts.Length < 2 )
{
                if ("".Equals(virtualDirectory))
                {
                    // Special case for unnamed controller with no virtual directory
                    parts = new String[] { "", parts[0] };
                }
                else
                {
                    throw new UrlTokenizerException("Invalid url");
                }
}
